Guy T. HELVERING, Commissioner of Internal Revenue, v. MADRID SUPPLY COMPANY. No. 1057. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. March 21, 1934. Robert H. Jackson, Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Hodges, Wilson & Rogers, of Denver, Colo., for respondent.

Before LEWIS, PHILLIPS, and Me-DERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition dismissed on motion of petitioner.
